What is the projected market size & growth rate of the AR and VR in Training Market?

Market Analysis and Size

Augmented Reality (AR) and Virtual Reality (VR) revolutionize training by immersing users in simulated environments. AR overlays digital content onto the real world, enhancing training with contextual information and interactive guidance. VR transports users to entirely virtual worlds, offering hands-on experiences and realistic simulations for training purposes.

Global AR and VR in training market was valued at USD 2094.08 billion in 2023 and is expected to reach USD 139343.56 billion by 2031, registering a CAGR of 69.00% during the forecast period of 2024-2031. “Component” segments accounts the highest market share owing to the increasing usage of AR and VR among the consumer. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

